1
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:05,400
MAN: Gonzo.

2
00:00:17,240 --> 00:00:19,880
KAZUMA (VOICEOVER): Eyes
as blue as the azure sky.

3
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:22,560
That is the symbol
of the Contractor.

4
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:24,920
Entrusted by the
Spirit King of the Wind

5
00:00:24,920 --> 00:00:29,040
with the powers of his
domain, I bear this mark,

6
00:00:29,040 --> 00:00:30,920
the stigma of the wind.

7
00:00:30,920 --> 00:02:14,640
[THEME ‐ SAORI KIUJI, "BLAST OF
WIND"]

8
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,640
[CHATTER]

9
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:23,600
AYANO (VOICEOVER): He's late.

10
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,000
How could he do this?

11
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,600
That idiot probably
doesn't even own a watch.

12
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:28,600
Is something wrong, Ayano?

13
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:30,040
You look kind of mad.

14
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:30,800
What?

15
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,720
No, no, nothing's wrong.

16
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:33,080
Are you kidding me?

17
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:33,880
MISAO: We have a visitor.

18
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:41,760
Well, it's about time.

19
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:43,560
There you are, Kazuma.

20
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:44,600
Come in.

21
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:45,480
Please sit down.

22
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:54,560
Guess I'm kind of late, huh?

23
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,400
No.

24
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:58,800
We're very happy that
you've decided to join us.

25
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:02,120
As you know, this young man is
Kazuma Yagami, who we must all

26
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,800
thank for his
invaluable assistance

27
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,320
in dealing with the Fuga clan.

28
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:06,280
Invaluable nothing.

29
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:08,320
We had to play him.

30
00:03:08,320 --> 00:03:09,240
Uh‐‐

31
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,120
Hey, Kazuma!

32
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:10,880
[CHUCKLE]

33
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:13,560
I'm so happy you're
finally here.

34
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,520
[GRUMBLE]

35
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,240
Do you want anything to drink?

36
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:17,880
I didn't come here
because I'm thirsty.

37
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,400
You're going to eat
with us, though, right?

38
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,920
I didn't come here
for food either.

39
00:03:20,920 --> 00:03:23,360
Huh?

40
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,720
You're acting
like a real jerk.

41
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,040
Is that what you came here for?

42
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,200
You're blocking my view.

43
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:33,840
Aren't you‐‐

44
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,200
I know you.

45
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:45,040
Masayuki's daughter, right?

46
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:47,480
Yes, that's right,
and Takeya's sister.

47
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:50,600
To show my appreciation, I
will attend to your every need.

48
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,240
So feel free to ask
me for anything.

49
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:58,320
Ask you for anything, huh?

50
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:03,280
I'll do anything you want.

51
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:10,080
Back off, you pervert!

52
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,400
Ugh!

53
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,200
No way!

54
00:04:12,200 --> 00:04:13,360
I won't let you touch her.

55
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:15,800
So you're just gonna have
to find someone else.

56
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,240
What's wrong with you, Misao?

57
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,120
Have a little self‐respect.

58
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:21,160
Don't degrade yourself for a
worthless scumbag like him.

59
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:24,400
Nice to hear you have such a
high opinion of me, princess.

60
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,080
Thank you, but you
really don't have to be

61
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,720
so protective of me, Ayano.

62
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:30,240
I'm offering myself to Kazuma
to thank him for putting an end

63
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:32,680
to the Fuga clan's uprising.

64
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,880
We wouldn't be alive today
if it weren't for him.

65
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:38,000
And he took revenge for
the death of my brother.

66
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,520
I'm willing to do anything
to repay him for that.

67
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:41,880
He's already been
paid with money.

68
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,600
So believe me, he's just fine.

69
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,320
A simple thank‐you
would be good enough.

70
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:46,800
You shouldn't thank me.

71
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:49,240
Doesn't really make much sense.

72
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,640
I mean, what do you
have to be grateful for?

73
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:54,800
After all, I'm responsible
for your brother's death.

74
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,360
What did you say?

75
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:58,120
Ryuya killed him,
but I definitely

76
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:59,680
made it easier to do.

77
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:02,760
If I hadn't knocked
Takeya unconscious,

78
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:04,800
then Ryuya might not
have been able to pick

79
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:07,840
him off so quickly.

80
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:09,920
Of course, even when
he was conscious,

81
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:13,320
he was no match for Ryuya.

82
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:16,400
Anyway, I understand if
you want to blame me.

83
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,640
So you can go ahead
and use the blade

84
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,720
you got hidden in your sleeve.

85
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:19,560
[GASP]

86
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,160
[SHOUTING]

87
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:23,880
[GASP]

88
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:31,160
No.

89
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:33,120
Kazuma.

90
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,560
Are you all right?

91
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,800
Say something.

92
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:37,920
You feel better now?

93
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:47,160
Father, this would probably
be a good time for you

94
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:49,480
to step in and do something.

95
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:52,040
Kazuma.

96
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,120
If you're unwilling
to punish Misao,

97
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,880
then it becomes necessary for us
to take the appropriate action.

98
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:01,440
Masayuki, I ask you as her
father, do you approve?

99
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,240
Yes.

100
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,760
As a member of the
Kannagi family,

101
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:06,240
Misao will accept full
responsibility for this,

102
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:08,600
as I'm sure she's prepared to.

103
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:11,880
KAZUMA: Don't you think you're
all kind of overreacting?

104
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,600
It's not like she killed me.

105
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:15,240
She couldn't hurt
me if she tried.

106
00:06:15,240 --> 00:06:17,200
Then if you do not
wish to punish her,

107
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:19,120
we will respect your decision.

108
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:22,480
However, we cannot permit
such inexcusable behavior.

109
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,440
And therefore, I'm
afraid we will have

110
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:26,400
to suspend Misao for a time.

111
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,400
It's not fair!

112
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:28,360
It should have been you.

113
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,680
Why did this have to happen?

114
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:31,360
Why did my brother have to die?

115
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:33,520
KAZUMA: Because he was weak.

116
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:35,560
Kazuma.

117
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,280
If that was supposed
to be some kind of joke,

118
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:39,280
then you've got a really
sick sense of humor.

119
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:41,720
How could you say
something so disrespectful?

120
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,760
Have you already forgotten
how weak you were

121
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:45,360
and what it felt like
before you discovered

122
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,800
how to use wind magic?

123
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,720
Are you done?

124
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,520
Because I am.

125
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,520
[QUIET WHIMPER]

126
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:01,040
[CAR HONKS]

127
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,520
YUKARI: Wow, look at her face.

128
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:06,240
And she's not even
joking around with us.

129
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:08,480
She's definitely in a rare
mood today, isn't she?

130
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:10,840
I know, and she didn't
waste any time on that guy who

131
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,440
tried to talk to us earlier.
‐ [GRUNT]

132
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,360
[GROAN]

133
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:16,880
Hey, are you talking about me?

134
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:18,280
Fess up, Ayano.

135
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,080
There's something going
on between you and a guy,

136
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,520
am I right?

137
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:22,760
Whoa.
What?

138
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:23,800
Where did that come from?

139
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,200
That doesn't make
any sense, you guys.

140
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,840
Oh, wow, so it's true?

141
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:28,320
No, that's not it at all.

142
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,120
It's no big deal.

143
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,160
You can tell us the truth.

144
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,000
So what's he like?

145
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:31,760
Is he cute?

146
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:33,280
Dude, enough!

147
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,120
Oh, come on.

148
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:34,880
Just give up.

149
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,680
There's no way Yukari's
going to let you off the hook

150
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,280
until you come clean with us.

151
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,160
She's right.

152
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:41,560
I already told
you, there's no guy!

153
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,000
Well, what a surprise.

154
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,800
Ayano making a scene again.

155
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:51,040
Hey, what are you doing here?

156
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,440
Wait, you know him?

157
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,400
You think he's the one?

158
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:56,920
You know, this might not
be the best place to be

159
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:58,200
drawing attention to yourself.

160
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,160
[GASP]

161
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:07,280
Oh, I guess I didn't
realize this place is‐‐

162
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:10,640
So Kazuma, is she one
of your little girlfriends

163
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,200
or something?

164
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,200
[GROAN]

165
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:16,240
No, Kirika, she's more
like the exact opposite.

166
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:18,320
She's just a distant
relative of mine.

167
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,680
Oh, is that so?

168
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,480
Then why is she so angry?

169
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,480
Don't know.

170
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:24,040
Think she was just
born that way.

171
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:26,520
What did you just say?

172
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:28,440
Ayano, you kids really
shouldn't be hanging

173
00:08:28,440 --> 00:08:30,760
out in this neighborhood.

174
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:31,760
[CHUCKLE]

175
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:34,800
[GROWL]

176
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:37,680
Guess if I fell in love with a
guy like that, I'd be confused.

177
00:08:37,680 --> 00:08:38,480
Yeah, right.

178
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,480
I totally don't get it.

179
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:41,120
He seems like the kind of
guy she normally hates.

180
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,760
Ugh!
That's it!

181
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:44,760
Tell me what you two are
whispering about now.

182
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:46,520
We're talking about
your new boyfriend, duh.

183
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:47,720
Though it looks
like you two haven't

184
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,280
started dating exclusively.

185
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:51,200
Will you please shut up?

186
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,880
How could I possibly
date that jerk?

187
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:55,240
I hate him more than anybody
I've ever met in my life!

188
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,200
Argh!
‐ Really?

189
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,600
Then what's with
the jealous fit?

190
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:58,400
What?

191
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:01,280
Well, uh, that's because I‐‐

192
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,080
I don't like him.

193
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,560
Now get off my back already!

194
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:04,400
[CHUCKLE]
Oh, yeah.

195
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:05,200
You know what?

196
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,560
I just realized
I've got this thing

197
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,560
I've got to do somewhere else.

198
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,440
I should really get going.

199
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,560
OK, bye!

200
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:10,400
[SIGH]

201
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,560
Talk about dodging
the question.

202
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:14,040
Yup, fleeing the scene.

203
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:15,840
But yeah, I think
you're exactly right.

204
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:18,240
She was totally acting
jealous, wasn't she?

205
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,920
Crazy thing is I don't think
she even realizes it herself.

206
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,080
How is that possible?

207
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,880
She'd have to be pretty
out of touch with reality

208
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,200
not to notice a thing like that.

209
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,280
We are talking about Ayano.

210
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:29,480
Then I've got a sneaking
suspicion that this is only

211
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,000
going to get more interesting.

212
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,080
You might just be right.

213
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,000
[BOTH GIGGLE]

214
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,720
AYANO (VOICEOVER): I
can't believe them.

215
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:39,280
Where would they get the
idea that I liked him anyway?

216
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:42,160
I don't even understand how
someone could like that guy.

217
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,680
I was just angry because
he was being a jerk.

218
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:46,440
What was he doing in
that kind of neighborhood

219
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,320
in the first place?

220
00:09:47,320 --> 00:09:49,320
And who the heck was
that girl he was with?

221
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:52,240
Why were they walking
so close together?

222
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,240
[GASP]

223
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:55,680
And what were they
doing in that hotel?

224
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:56,680
Were they‐‐

225
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:57,640
[WHIMPER]

226
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:00,640
about to‐‐

227
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,600
That scumbag!

228
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,600
Where the heck did he go?

229
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:08,440
Oh, hey.

230
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,360
How's it going, Ayano?

231
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:10,240
What are you up to?

232
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,400
I need you to meet me now.

233
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,200
Why?

234
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:14,160
Just get over
here and help me!

235
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:31,240
(PANTING) Can't we
please take a break?

236
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:33,760
There's no way we're going to
find him in a busy neighborhood

237
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:34,920
like this.

238
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:37,560
We don't have tracking skills
on wind magic users too.

239
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:40,400
Sounds like the only skill
you have is whining, Ren.

240
00:10:40,400 --> 00:10:42,560
Now that I think about
it, instead of dragging me

241
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,480
all over town to find
Kazuma, why didn't you just

242
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:46,120
call him on his cell phone?

243
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:48,360
Why would I even have
that guy's cell number?

244
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:50,440
And besides, I don't
want to talk to him.

245
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:53,200
Ayano, can we please rest
for just a little while?

246
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,520
I'm begging you, please.

247
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,680
I'm so thirs‐‐

248
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:56,640
AYANO: Oh, walk it off.

249
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:57,920
We don't have time to rest.

250
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:58,840
REN: Um‐‐

251
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,720
Huh?

252
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,200
I think I just found him.

253
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:06,880
Aah!

254
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:12,320
So, um, why are we
hiding behind a tree?

255
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:14,560
We just spent an
hour looking for him.

256
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:16,360
Don't worry about it.

257
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,640
Doesn't look like
he's with anyone.

258
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:18,440
Why?

259
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,200
Was he with somebody
else earlier?

260
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:23,480
Uh, no, I was just making
an observation, that's all.

261
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,440
REN: Although it
does kind of look

262
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:27,640
like he's waiting for somebody.

263
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:29,760
AYANO (VOICEOVER): Who
could he be waiting for?

264
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:30,600
REN: Here she comes.

265
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,480
[GASP]

266
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:34,560
[SAD SIGH]

267
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:37,560
Wow, she's kinda pretty.

268
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:38,840
Is that‐‐

269
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:40,000
Wait, that's Misao.

270
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:50,680
Yep, that's definitely her.

271
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:53,120
Do you think they're on a date?

272
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:55,120
[GROWLING]

273
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,560
Ayano, are you OK?

274
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:58,560
Let's go!

275
00:11:58,560 --> 00:11:59,560
[GROAN]

276
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:13,440
Don't you think we're a
little close right now?

277
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,240
They're going to see us.

278
00:12:14,240 --> 00:12:15,280
AYANO: Will you stop grumbling?

279
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,600
REN: They're
obviously on a date.

280
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,400
Now, can we please
stop stalking them?

281
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,360
This is getting creepy.

282
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:20,280
We're not stalking them.

283
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:23,560
We're just secretly
following them.

284
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:25,000
[SIGH]

285
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:25,920
Something wrong, Kazuma?

286
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:27,200
You seem kinda distant.

287
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,080
Oh, no.

288
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:30,160
Everything's just fine.

289
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,120
We're almost there.

290
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:42,000
Why did he bring
her back here?

291
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,400
OK, I think
we've followed them

292
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:44,680
enough to know what's going on.

293
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:47,120
We've already come this far.
it's too late to turn back now.

294
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:47,920
Huh?

295
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:49,160
Come on, keeping moving.

296
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:49,920
Huh?

297
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,440
[GASP]

298
00:12:58,240 --> 00:13:00,160
Is that a hotel?

299
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:02,680
Seriously, Ayano, I don't
think I want to see any more.

300
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:03,920
[FLAMES IGNITE]

301
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:07,640
Perv, how could you?

302
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:11,600
Can we go home now?

303
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,120
[MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:17,080
[GROWLING]

305
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:21,200
Ayano, you should
try to breathe.

306
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:24,880
I can't believe he brought
her here to a place like this!

307
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:36,240
This is unforgivable!

308
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,200
Ayano, please calm down.

309
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,360
You got to control yourself!

310
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:42,160
Grr.

311
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,520
Hotel Campanera, huh?

312
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:48,320
What?

313
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,160
Something wrong?

314
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:50,200
It's OK.

315
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:52,920
This place is kind of a dump,
but I guess it's all right.

316
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,360
[GIGGLE]

317
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,200
Well, it's too late now.

318
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,160
You're here for good.

319
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:00,160
[GUNSHOT]

320
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:03,120
[GASP]

321
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,560
[GUNSHOTS]

322
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:06,520
[GRUNT]

323
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:09,000
[COCKING]

324
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,920
[GUNFIRE]

325
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:21,280
[BOOM]

326
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:27,200
Guess I was more of a threat
than you thought, wasn't I?

327
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,600
AYANO: You want to tell
me what's going on here?

328
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,840
Ayano.

329
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,640
Ren.

330
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,160
I'd hoped to avoid
any witnesses,

331
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,120
but maybe it's good
that you're here.

332
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:38,080
It seems appropriate that
a member of the family

333
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:40,120
should be here to
gather his remains.

334
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:41,200
His what?

335
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,400
Seriously?

336
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,320
Don't tell me you really
thought a lame attack

337
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:45,920
like that could kill Kazuma.

338
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:48,200
I doubt you even put a
single scratch on him.

339
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,160
[GASP]

340
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:53,520
Oh no, that's impossible.

341
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:54,520
[GASP]

342
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,360
[MEN SCREAMING]

343
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:05,160
Yeah, it's much
nicer here now.

344
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:06,560
[THUMPING]

345
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:12,440
Hey, don't even bother.

346
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:16,080
I already had a little talk
with your rooftop sniper.

347
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,120
MISAO: What?

348
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:17,880
How could you‐‐

349
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:19,040
Don't feel too bad.

350
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:21,200
It was a good idea in theory.

351
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:23,040
I was almost surprised.

352
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:25,880
And weapons are more
effective than your magic.

353
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:28,160
Only thing is you'll
need more guns.

354
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:34,360
You've changed, huh?

355
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:36,160
Did I make you this way?

356
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:37,720
Are you serious?

357
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:39,240
You haven't seen me in 10 years.

358
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:43,560
You really think you know me
well enough to even ask that?

359
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:45,120
OK, good point.

360
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:45,880
All right, you too.

361
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:47,120
That's enough with the chatter.

362
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,280
Misao, you're
coming home with me.

363
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:50,680
You're going to
explain everything

364
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:51,840
you've done to my father.

365
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:56,040
Hey!

366
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:56,880
Get back here!

367
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:57,680
Wait!

368
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:09,880
She's right.

369
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:10,760
10 years.

370
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:17,360
[HURRIED FOOTSTEPS]

371
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:26,000
You've cornered
yourself, Misao.

372
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:26,920
Just give up.

373
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:28,480
You're not going to
get away from me.

374
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:30,720
You're chasing after me like
I'm some kind of criminal,

375
00:16:30,720 --> 00:16:33,440
and I haven't done
anything wrong.

376
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:34,720
Now, leave me alone.

377
00:16:34,720 --> 00:16:36,360
Don't try to
play dumb with me.

378
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,640
I was standing right there.

379
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:39,560
Do you even realize
what you've done?

380
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:40,600
What?

381
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:43,200
You hired mercenaries
to gun down an ally

382
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:46,000
of the Kannagi family,
and that's unforgivable.

383
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,040
As the next head of
the family, I can't

384
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:49,560
let you get away with this.

385
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:50,640
Misao, please.

386
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:51,720
Just come home.

387
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,920
I won't be punished for
doing something the rest

388
00:16:53,920 --> 00:16:56,240
of the family was scared to do.

389
00:16:56,240 --> 00:16:58,200
Then you've left
me with no choice.

390
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,560
Enraiha, come forth!

391
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:15,720
That's enough.

392
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:18,200
You girls are going to get
heard playing that way.

393
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,720
It's Kazuma.

394
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:21,080
Oh, great.

395
00:17:21,080 --> 00:17:23,360
I've got this under
control, all right?

396
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:26,240
Look, I'm just
returning her purse.

397
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:28,240
That's got to be the worst
excuse I've ever heard.

398
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:30,680
Ayano, you're taking
this a little too far.

399
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:32,640
Misao didn't do anything
to the Kannagi family.

400
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:33,840
She tried to kill me.

401
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:36,120
So I don't see how it's
any of your business.

402
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:37,320
You're missing the point.

403
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:39,440
Misao is a member of
the Kannagi family,

404
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:41,080
and her actions
reflect on all of us.

405
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:42,320
Don't you get that?

406
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:46,360
No, I guess I don't.

407
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:47,600
I mean it.

408
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:50,280
What happened here is
between Misao and me.

409
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,120
So just leave it alone.

410
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:51,880
What?

411
00:17:51,880 --> 00:17:54,040
You can't be serious, Kazuma.

412
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:56,320
You're talking about a girl
that just tried to kill you.

413
00:17:56,320 --> 00:17:59,760
And if you do anything to stop
her, she's going to try again!

414
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:00,720
And I don't care.

415
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:01,520
What?

416
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:02,680
Why not?

417
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,240
Because it doesn't matter.

418
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:05,760
She can't even put
a scratch on me.

419
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:13,360
Hah!

420
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,800
It's pointless, Misao.

421
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:20,680
Can't you see that?

422
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:21,760
Just let it go.

423
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:23,080
He's too strong for you.

424
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:26,200
You have nowhere near the
same level of magic he does.

425
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,720
How could you?

426
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:31,120
It's not fair.

427
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:32,560
Argh!

428
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:35,000
Why did you kill my brother?

429
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:35,920
You killed him!

430
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:37,840
This is all your fault!

431
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:39,280
You took him from me.

432
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:41,720
You killed my precious Takeya!

433
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:46,120
He was the only person in my
family that cared about me,

434
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:48,080
and you killed him.

435
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:51,000
He was the only
one that I loved!

436
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,000
Why did you kill him?

437
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:56,360
Why'd you have to
take him away from me?

438
00:18:56,360 --> 00:18:58,920
You have to learn to
be strong for me, Misao.

439
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:01,440
I need to know that you
can take care of yourself.

440
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:03,400
But why, Takeya?

441
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,600
I'm not on my own.

442
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:05,520
You're here.

443
00:19:05,520 --> 00:19:09,200
I know I'll always
have you to protect me.

444
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:10,680
I hope you're right.

445
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:15,680
[GRUNTING]

446
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:30,160
[WHIMPERING]

447
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,160
[SOBBING]

448
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:53,200
I'll never forgive you
for what you've done.

449
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,400
Never.

450
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:58,480
And I will do anything it takes
to make you suffer like he did.

451
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,440
Do what you have to do.

452
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,440
Are you OK?

453
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:12,880
Hey, wait.

454
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:13,680
Kazuma.

455
00:21:02,240 --> 00:21:05,480
What is it you wish for?

456
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:07,360
Is it the death of another?

457
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:10,000
Do you seek vengeance?

458
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:14,680
Or do you simply hunger for
an unstoppable strength?

459
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,640
All of them.

460
00:21:16,640 --> 00:21:18,000
[CHUCKLE]

461
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:21,080
You're a greedy little girl.

462
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:22,520
Ambitious.

463
00:21:22,520 --> 00:21:26,720
But if that is what you desire,
I will grant your wishes.

464
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:29,240
Now, look at me.

465
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:54,600
[GASP]

466
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,440
What's happening?

467
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:02,880
[GASP]

468
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,840
[PANTING]

469
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:08,360
[GRUNT]

470
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:14,800
No!

471
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,760
[MUFFLED SCREAMING]

472
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:25,800
All right.

473
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:28,320
Let's begin.

474
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,480
Yes, please.

475
00:22:29,480 --> 00:22:30,720
Help me, angel.

476
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:37,200
[THEME ‐ SAORI KIUJI, "HITORI
KIRI NO SORA"]

477
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:07,680
AYANO (VOICEOVER): Did you
just call me a burden, Kazuma?

478
00:24:07,680 --> 00:24:09,400
I'll show you a
burden, you idiot.

479
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:10,840
Just wait until
you need my help.

480
00:24:10,840 --> 00:24:12,320
You could be dying
for all I care.

481
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:13,680
I'll never help you again!

482
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:14,480
Wait a minute.

483
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:16,120
You want me to do what?

484
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:18,560
You want to use me as bait?

485
00:24:18,560 --> 00:24:20,000
Are you out of your mind?

486
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:23,280
How dare you ask me to do that!

487
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:26,840
Next time on "Kaze no
Stigma," "The Price of Power."

488
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:31,120
Misao, can't you even see what
you're doing to your aura?

